question.title: Will the average daily price of kerosene jet fuel in the US Gulf Coast be greater than $2.50 per gallon in March 2026?
question.description:
This question tracks whether the monthly average of the 'U.S. Gulf Coast Jet Fuel Spot Price FOB' exceeds $2.50 per gallon for the month of March 2026, as reported by the U.S. Energy Information Administration (EIA).

`{"format":"bot_tournament_question","info":{"hash_id":"df8afcea30f28637","sheet_id":56.1}}`
question.resolution_criteria: This question resolves to Yes if the monthly average for the 'U.S Gulf Coast Kerosene-Type Jet Fuel' for the month of March 2026 is strictly greater than $2.500 per gallon, as reported by the U.S. Energy Information Administration (EIA). If the reported value is $2.500 or less, the question resolves to No. According to https://www.eia.gov/dnav/pet/hist/eer_epjk_pf4_rgc_dpgD.htm
question.fine_print: The resolution will be based on the monthly average data published by the EIA at https://www.eia.gov/dnav/pet/hist/LeafHandler.ashx?n=PET&s=EER_EPJK_PF4_RGC_DPG&f=M. If the EIA revises the data after Metaculus resolves it, the question will not re-resolve.
